Automatic Monthly Attendance Data Extraction and Management Tool, TUTORIAL¶

Prerequisites:¶

  1. Before running the tool make sure that each individual participant has their own time sheet in their own respective folder.
  2. Make sure that the file name that is in each folder is the same as well.

Usage:¶

Step 1: Install Dependencies¶

To install the necessary Python libraries, run the following command by clicking on the play buton on the left:

Step 2: Mount Google Drive and Starting the Script¶

Like how you ran the snippet from before in step one do the same for the next code snippet. The script needs access to Google Drive. Don't worry; it's easy to set up! Refer to the following images below to mount your Google Drive. This step ensures that the script can access and save files to your Google Drive account. Note: The image only shows a portion of the code!

1. Running the script¶

2. Connect to Google Drive. It will open a new window asking for access.¶

3. Select the account associated.¶

4. Give accesss so that the script can run properly and mount the Google Drive¶

Step 3:Enter the File Name¶

When prompted, type the name of the individual timesheet file, including the .docx extension (e.g., "9-2023 Participant Timesheet.docx"). If you're not sure, don't worry; it will remind you of the correct format.

After entering file name the program will ask a series of questions. Simply type your answer in the box and press enter.¶

Step 4: Finish¶

After following the prompts the program will finish and you can check for the Monthly time sheet in the folder on your Google Drive.

Below you can see that it created an excel file with its own name based on the data extracted from the Docx files.¶

  3. Have access to Google Drive account

Usage:¶
